Key Match Events: Liam Livingstone smashed 87 in his 50th T20 international to ensure England levelled the series 1-1 with an over remaining.
Phil Salt hit three successive sixes in the third over
Sean Abbott took two quick wickets in the fourth over
Jake Fraser-McGurk caught Will Jacks for 12
Jordan Cox was bowled for a second ball duck
Livingstone took England to the brink with a six and a four but was then caught by Matt Short with one run required
Adil Rashid closed the game out with a single and six balls remaining
